===Noun===
'''Atropine'''
{{wikipedia}}

#An [[alkaloid]] extracted from the plant [[deadly nightshade]] (''Atropa belladonna'') and other sources.  Though overdoses would be fatal it is used as a [[drug]] in medicine for its [[paralytic]] effects (e.g. in surgery to relax muscles, in dentistry to dry the mouth, in [[opthalmatry]] to dialate the [[pupil]]s).

